# Implementation Plan - Modern Tasks (Day 1)

**Goal:** Create a modern, beautiful ToDo app using Jetpack Compose to master the basics of Android UI 2025.

## User Review Required
> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Project Creation**: Since Android projects require complex Gradle setups and binary wrappers, **you must create the base project in Android Studio first**.
> I will then generate the Kotlin source files and resources.

## Proposed Changes

### Project Setup (User Action)
1.  Open Android Studio.
2.  New Project -> **Empty Activity**.
3.  Name: `ModernTasks`
4.  Package: `com.kerenlint.moderntasks` (or similar, please confirm).
5.  Language: **Kotlin**.
6.  Build Configuration: **Kotlin DSL (build.gradle.kts)**.

### Code Structure (I will generate these)
We will adopt a clean package structure from Day 1.

#### [NEW] `ui/theme`
- `Color.kt`: Define a modern, vibrant color palette (not default purple).
- `Type.kt`: Modern typography.
- `Theme.kt`: Dark/Light mode support.

#### [NEW] `model`
- `TodoItem.kt`: Data class for a task.

#### [NEW] `ui/components`
- `TodoItemRow.kt`: A beautiful composable for a single list item.
- `TodoList.kt`: LazyColumn for the list.
- `AddTodoFab.kt`: Floating Action Button with animation.

#### [MODIFY] `MainActivity.kt`
- Set up the main `Scaffold`.
- Integrate the components.

